<p>Next time let’s go together…ㅠㅠ and present your research at the international conference!!</p>]]></content><author><name>trevon-badloe</name></author><category term="conference," /><category term="invitedtalk," /><category term="Korea" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The A3 Metamaterials Forum 2025 international conference was held at KAIST, Daejeon, Korea, bringing leading researchers in the field of metamaterials from the 3 countries of East Asia, Korea, Japan, and China!]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://metai.korea.ac.kr/images/news/2025/07/A3%20Metamaterials%2005/A3_names.jpeg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://metai.korea.ac.kr/images/news/2025/07/A3%20Metamaterials%2005/A3_names.jpeg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Trevon visited Nanjing and Suzhou in China!~</title><link href="https://metai.korea.ac.kr/2025/06/28/NJUST-Suzhou-25.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Trevon visited Nanjing and Suzhou in China!~" /><published>2025-06-28T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-12-02T16:15:20+00:00</updated><id>https://metai.korea.ac.kr/2025/06/28/NJUST-Suzhou-25</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://metai.korea.ac.kr/2025/06/28/NJUST-Suzhou-25.html"><![CDATA[<p>Trevon spent 10 days at Nanjing University of Science and Technology (NJUST), China, hosted by Profs. Xuefeng Liu and Jichuan Xiong from the School of Electronic Engineering and Optoelectronics Technology, as well as a couple of days visiting Suzhou City University in Suzhou…</p>

